            <div type="note">
                <head type="title">Lesson</head>
                <p>A prose genre type developed initially by Richard Lovell Edgeworth and Honoria Edgeworth,
                    and developed by Maria Edgeworth, in order to demonstrate their educational theories to young readers. In the address "To Parents" prefacing part 3 of Harry and Lucy, 
                    the lesson is defined against the task, the latter characterized as "certain answers to certain questions by rote" (141-42 [1868]). <!--Entry needed here.-->.</p>
